				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Сказание (Skazanie)" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>&amp;#208;&amp;#161;&amp;#208;&amp;#186;&amp;#208;&amp;#176;&amp;#208;&amp;#183;&amp;#208;&amp;#176;&amp;#208;&amp;#189;&amp;#208;&amp;#184;&amp;#208;&amp;#181; (&amp;quot;Skazanie&amp;quot;) is a fast and dynamic game for 2-4 players. It is easy to learn and explain. This game will take its players on a journey through the ancient Slavic lands and ages long-past, and show them a world of powerful gods, mythical creatures and omens.&amp;#10;The game is played by drawing battle cards and magical cards. Each round consists of rolling a die to determine the player's strength and then playing a battle card, which adds even more strength to the die. Magical cards are utilised to further enhance a player's strength, or to affect negatively the opponent/opponents. The winner of the round is the player with the highest strength after each player has chosen their battle card and magical cards. The game ends when there are no cards left in the drawing piles. The player with the highest score (most rounds won) is considered the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
